<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I like to integrate Zend_Captcha in an old project - but i need to create an instance of Zend_View only to fit the first argument of Zend_Captcha_Adapter::render().</p>

&lt;?php

$captcha = new Zend_Captcha_Dump()
$id = $captcha-&gt;generate();
echo $captcha-&gt;render(new Zend_View());

?&gt;

<p>Would it not be better, to make the first argument optional? 
Currently no adapter use the first argument! Future one might - but they can check this and throw an exception if its not present.</p>

